1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 493, O.S.L.
2 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 698.4), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 698.4. A. As used in this section, "eligible school
5 district" means a public school district or public school district
6 foundation in this state that has established a program to provide
7 tuition or loan repayment assistance to school district employees
8 who pursue:
9 1. Pursue an undergraduate degree from a teacher preparation
10 program accredited by the Commission for Educational Quality and
11 Accountability leading to a standard teaching certificate; or
12 2. Are enrolled in nondegree-seeking coursework required for
13 completion of an approved alternative certification pathway from a
14 teacher preparation program accredited by the Commission for
15 Educational Quality and Accountability leading to a standard
16 teaching certificate.
17 B. There is hereby created the Grow Your Own Educator Program
18 to provide matching fund grants to eligible school districts. The
19 program shall be established and maintained by the State Department
20 of Education.
21 C. An eligible school district seeking to participate in the
22 Grow Your Own Educator Program shall submit an application in the
23 manner and on a form prescribed by the State Department of
24 Education. The application shall include:
Req. No. 17570 Page 2

1 1. The amount of matching fund grants requested;
2 2. The position of the employee pursuing an undergraduate
3 degree or alternate certification coursework from a teacher
4 preparation program; and
5 3. The subject area in which the employee is pursuing an
6 undergraduate degree or alternate certification from a teacher
7 preparation program.
8 D. Matching fund Fund grants shall be awarded on a first-come,
9 first-served basis. Grants shall be provided without any limitation
10 other than the amount of funds available in the Grow Your Own
11 Educator Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2 of this act
12 and the number of eligible school districts that apply.
13 E. By June 30, 2026 2027, and each June 30 thereafter, an
14 eligible school district that receives a matching fund grant
15 pursuant to this section shall electronically submit a report to the
16 State Department of Education that includes:
17 1. A status update on the progress the employee receiving
18 tuition assistance is making in the teacher preparation program in
19 which he or she is enrolled; or
20 2. The employment status of the employee receiving loan
21 repayment assistance.
22 F. By December 31, 2026 2027, and each December 31 thereafter,
23 the State Department of Education shall electronically submit a
24
Req. No. 17570 Page 3

1 repo rt to the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and
2 the Speaker of the House of Representatives that includes:
3 1. The school district matching fund grant recipients;
4 2. The amount of matching fund grants allocated to each
5 recipient;
6 3. The subject area in which the employee receiving tuition
7 assistance is pursuing an undergraduate degree, or the subject area
8 in which the employee receiving loan repayment assistance has
9 received an undergraduate degree; and
10 4. The information submitted pursuant to subsection E of this
11 section.
12 G. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules to
13 implement the provisions of this section.
14 H. 1. Employees enrolled in an approved alternative
15 certification pathway as described in subsection A of this section
16 shall be eligible for tuition or course fee reimbursement through
17 the Grow Your Own Educator Program.
18 2. Eligible coursework for alternative certification may
19 include, but is not limited to, classes in classroom management,
20 pedagogy, student assessment, special education, and instructional
21 methodology, as determined by the State Department of Education.
22 3. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules to
23 identify and approve eligible nondegree-seeking courses and
24 alternative certification programs that qualify under this section.
Req. No. 17570 Page 4

1 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
